      {
        "title": "Warblade",
        "excerpt": "Warblades are specialist fighters who develop a unique personal fighting style. Every warblade is completely different from every other warblade, as they all develop distinct and specialized weapons and fighting styles. Warblades usually trained at small esoteric martial arts schools with few practitioners.   Warblade talents use weapons for unique or customizable martial maneuvers. Warblades can specialize in any combination of offense, defense, and utility, depending on what maneuvers they choose. Warblade ribbons represent unique or strange skills associated with their particular fighting style.   Examples of warblades in fiction include almost all anime fighters that have unique or strange fighting styles, as well as almost all characters from classic arcade fighting games.     Powers          Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Combo Move                  Novice                                                              You chain another attack onto a successful combo                                               Empowered Strike                  Novice                                                              You empower yourself with a burst of speed and strength                                               Exotic Weapon                  Novice                                      You have a special exotic weapon with unique properties                                               Fighting Style                  Novice                                      You specialize in a particular style of combat                                               Versatile Style                  Novice                                                              You can instantly master all kinds of weapons                                               Iron Heart Surge                  Veteran                                                              You break free of all negative effects afflicting you                                               Call Weapon                  Ribbon                                                              You call your bonded weapon to your hand from any distance                                               Damage Mastery                  Ribbon                                      You can deal any type of damage with any weapon                                               Overconfidence                  Ribbon                                      You have an unfailing belief in your own combat prowess                                               Style Master                  Ribbon                                      You have a reputation as the master of a martial arts style                  Talents                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Combo Move                                   Novice                                  Trigger         You get a critical success on a Strike                  Make a Strike against the target of the triggering Strike.                                           Empowered Strike                                   Novice                                Encounter               Make a Strike. This Strike deals an extra 1d10 damage on a success.   When you get a critical success on a Strike, this power refreshes, letting you use it again without taking a 5-minute rest.                                           Exotic Weapon                         Novice                 You have a unique exotic weapon. Choose two weapons (other than unarmed). Your exotic weapon counts as either or both weapons, whatever is most beneficial. For example, if your exotic weapon combines a dagger and a heavy weapon, then you could treat your exotic weapon as a Finesse One-Handed weapon that deals 1d12 Piercing base damage.   Only you can wield your exotic weapon. If you ever lose your exotic weapon, you can obtain a replacement when you complete an 8-hour rest.                                           Fighting Style                         Novice                 When you learn this power, choose one of the following effects.      Aggressor   Your Speed is doubled during the first round of each encounter   Blind Fighter   The blinded condition doesn’t make you flat-footed or impose disadvantage on your attack rolls   Executioner   You have a +2 bonus to attacks against bloodied targets   Mariner   You have a Swim Speed equal to your Speed, and you have a +1 bonus to Agility DC   Opportunist   You have a +2 bonus to attacks against targets are that restrained, slowed, or stunned   Weapon Master   Your first Strike each encounter with each weapon type deals an extra +2 damage on a success                                           Versatile Style                                   Novice                                Stance               You learn one combat feat of your choice.                                           Iron Heart Surge                                   Veteran                                Daily                                Duration         1 minute                  Choose any number of powers currently affecting you. You are immune to the effects of this use of those powers. Future uses of those powers can still affect you, and those powers can still affect other creatures.   You can use Iron Heart Surge even when an effect would normally stop you from using it.                                                                     Ribbons                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          Call Weapon                                   Ribbon                                Encounter               Your bonded weapon instantly teleports into your hand. This power works no matter the distance between you and your bonded weapon.   You can bond with a new weapon by conducting a 1-hour ritual involving the new weapon. You can only have one bonded weapon at a time.                                           Damage Mastery                         Ribbon                 When your Strike would deal Bludgeoning, Piercing, or Slashing damage, you can replace that trait with a different one from that list.                                           Overconfidence                         Ribbon                 You have advantage on Spirit rolls made to convince other people of your combat ability through words and appearance.                                           Style Master                         Ribbon                                Reputation               You have a reputation as a martial artist who has mastered a particular style. Other people know of your skill and may seek you out for training in this style.",
        "url": "/warblade.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Acrobat",
        "excerpt": "Acrobats are agile combatants who leap and dodge between attacks. They move through the front line with ease, dodging enemy attacks and retaliating with speed and precision. Acrobats are known for their supernatural abilities to move on difficult terrain, running up walls, along water, or even walking on thin air.   Acrobat talents focus on movement and dodging attacks. The majority of acrobat talents are defensive, though a few give opportunities to disorient enemies or counterattack. Some acrobat talents combine movement and combat, giving stat bonuses for using the environment to your advantage. Acrobat talents give even more ways to move around the world.   Examples of acrobats in fiction include Ty Lee from Avatar: The Last Airbender, Spiderman from Marvel Comics, all the protagonists of Assassin’s Creed, and most fictional monks and swashbucklers.     Powers          Name     Tier     Type     Description                                      Aerial Artistry                  Novice                                      You easily leap and jump over obstacles and into the air                                               Evasive Dash                  Novice                                                              You dash like the wind, becoming impossible to hit                                               Incredible Movement                  Novice                                      You can run at incredible, almost superhuman speeds                                               Leap Attack                  Novice                                                              You can leap through the air while attacking                                               Skirmish                  Novice                                                              You can evade enemies that try to approach close to you                                               Stunning Strike                  Novice                                                                                                             Uncanny Dodge                  Veteran                                                              You can evade the worst hurt from potentially deadly attacks                                               Contortionist                  Ribbon                                      You can contort your body to squeeze into tiny spaces                                               Slow Fall                  Ribbon                                                              You maneuver yourself in midair to reduce the damage of a fall                                               Quick Climb                  Ribbon                                      You can climb up vertical surfaces as fast as you can run                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Talents                          Aerial Artistry                         Novice                 When you Stride, you can choose to make two short leaps instead of moving normally. For each leap, fly a distance through the air equal to half your Speed. You must end each leap on a creature, solid object, or the ground. If you do not, you fall and your Stride ends.                                           Evasive Dash                                   Novice                                  Duration         Until the start of your next turn                  Use the Stride power. You gain +1 Defense and Agility DC for each 10 feet you move after using this power. For example, if you use this power and Stride 30 feet, then Stride 30 more feet, then fall 20 feet, you have a total of +8 Defense and Agility DC.                                           Incredible Movement                         Novice                 While you’re wearing light clothing, you gain a bonus to your Speed equal to 5 feet * your Acrobat level.                                           Leap Attack                                   Novice                                Move               You jump up to 30 feet in a straight line. You can use other powers in the middle of this jump. You have a +2 bonus to your next melee Strike before the end of your turn.                                           Skirmish                                   Novice                                  Trigger         A hostile creature uses a Move power to move to a space adjacent to you                  Stride at half Speed.                                           Stunning Strike                                   Novice                                Encounter                                Duration         Until the end of your next turn                  Make a melee Strike. On a success, your target is flat-footed. On a critical success, your target is stunned instead.                                           Uncanny Dodge                                   Veteran                                  Trigger         You are targeted by an attack                  You take half damage from the triggering attack.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 Ribbons                                                                                                              Contortionist                         Ribbon                 You count as a creature half your size when trying to fit into small areas.                                           Slow Fall                                   Ribbon                                  Trigger         You fall and hit the ground                  You reduce the fall damage you would take by 10 + 5 * your Acrobat level.                                           Quick Climb                         Ribbon                 You can climb at your full Speed instead of at half Speed.",
        "url": "/acrobat.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Hunter",
        "excerpt": "Hunters are ranged warriors who focus on taking down targets with precise, deadly shots. They are unmatched when it comes to chasing and defeating single targets, as enemies can’t flee from their range and accuracy. Most hunters avoid fighting in melee, preferring to use their range to their advantage.   Hunter talents give a variety of boosts to ranged weapons and single-target attacks. Some talents give buffs to single long-range shots with high accuracy and damage, while others give buffs to attacks against specific targets. Hunter ribbons give them bonuses on tracking down enemies and surviving the wilderness.   Examples of hunters in fiction include Hawkeye from Marvel Comics, Ashe from League of Legends, and most fictional rangers or snipers.     Powers          Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Bear Trap                  Novice                                                              You throw a portable bear trap towards a nearby enemy                                               Focus Aim                  Novice                                                              You steady your aim, preparing for a single strike                                               Hunt Prey                  Novice                                                              You focus on hunting down and attacking a single target                                               Sharpshooter                  Novice                                      You are an expert at making long range shots on difficult targets                                               Sniper's Shot                  Novice                                                              You make a long-range attack with increased accuracy and damage                                               Feral Senses                  Veteran                                      You can detect and fight nearby enemies even when you can’t see                                               Favored Enemy                  Ribbon                                      You are especially skilled at hunting down a particular kind of creature                                               Find Arrows                  Ribbon                                                              You’re always able to find or craft more ammunition                                               Pass Without Trace                  Ribbon                                      You can perfectly camouflage your tracks to avoid pursuers                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Talents                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Bear Trap                                   Novice                                Attack              Encounter                                Range         60 feet              Duration         Forever                  Make an Agility attack roll against your target’s Agility DC.                       Critical Success         Your target takes 3d6 damage and is restrained                   Success         Your target takes 2d6 damage and is immobilized                   Failure         Your target takes 1d6 damage and is slowed until the end of your next turn                                                       Focus Aim                                   Novice                                  Duration         1 minute, or until you use any Move power                  You have a +2 bonus to your next Strike. This bonus stacks with further uses of this power, up to a maximum of +6.                                           Hunt Prey                                   Novice                                Concentrate                                Target         One creature you can see, or one creature whose trail you’re following              Duration         24 hours, or until you use this power again                  You have advantage on die rolls made to search for or track your target. Your first Strike each round against your target deals an extra 1d6 damage.                                           Sharpshooter                         Novice                 You treat ranged weapons as having double their normal range, and you ignore cover when making ranged Strikes.                                           Sniper's Shot                                   Novice                                Encounter               Make a ranged Strike with a +5 bonus. This Strike doesn’t get disadvantage for being a long-range Strike.                                           Feral Senses                         Veteran                 You have blindsight to a distance of 30 feet.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Ribbons                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Favored Enemy                         Ribbon                 Choose a type of favored enemy: beasts, demons, dragons, elementals, fey, monstrosities, or undead. You can advantage on die rolls to track or recall information about your favored enemies. You also learn one language of your choice that is spoken by your favored enemies (if they don’t speak, you can learn any language of your choice).                                           Find Arrows                                   Ribbon                                Daily               You acquire a bundle of 50 arrows or bolts. This ammunition might be a set you constructed at a fletcher’s shop, a set you crafted from primitive natural materials, or a lucky find on the battlefield.                                           Pass Without Trace                         Ribbon                 You can hide your trail while travelling in natural environments, giving you a +10 bonus to any die rolls made to avoid being tracked.",
        "url": "/hunter.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Inventor",
        "excerpt": "Inventors are genius engineers who test their gadgets in the field. They design and build a variety of amazing or technologically impossible devices to fight enemies or accomplish tasks. An inventor’s gadgets might include robot minions, prototype firearms, or electrical circuits. Inventors ignore the normal technological level of the setting.   Inventor talents let them create gadgets that perform a variety of utility effects. These include everything from potions that heal injured allies to automatic turrets that attack enemies to grappling hooks to fly around. Inventor ribbons give them even more options for building objects with miscellaneous useful effects.   Examples of inventors in fiction include Iron Man from Marvel Comics, the Engineer from Team Fortress 2, and most fictional scientist or engineer heroes.     Powers          Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Automatic Turret                  Novice                                                              You construct a turret that can fire its cannon at enemies                                               Magitech Engine                  Novice                                                              You craft a small engine with an elemental effect                                               Shock Net                  Novice                                                              You throw an electrified net to restrain an enemy                                               Universal Gadget                  Novice                                                              You create a gadget that lets you replicate another talent                                               Upgrade Weapon                  Novice                                                              You upgrade an existing weapon with an additional effect                                               Overload                  Veteran                                                              You overload one of your creations with power, exploding it                                               Mystery Potion                  Ribbon                                                              You produce a mysterious potion with a chaotic, unpredictable effect                                               Robot Servant                  Ribbon                                      You created a robotic servant that completes simple tasks for you                                               Tinker                  Ribbon                                                              You quickly construct a small mechanical device to perform a simple task                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Talents                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Automatic Turret                                   Novice                                Concentrate              Manipulate                                Duration         10 minutes, or until you use this power again                  You set up an automatic turret on a flat surface you can reach. The turret is a Minion creature with (10 * your Inventor level) Health, 15 Defense, and 0 Speed. The turret’s Strength and Agility are equal to your Intellect, and it has no Intellect or Spirit stats. The turret can fire its cannon as a ranged weapon that deals 2d8 Piercing damage and has a range of 150 feet.                                           Magitech Engine                                   Novice                                Concentrate              Manipulate                                Duration         1 minute after the engine is attached to a weapon, or 1 hour otherwise                  You craft a small magic device that outputs a stream of elemental energy. Choose the engine’s element to be one of Acid, Cold, Electricity, Fire, Force, or Sonic. You can set up the engine to perform a minor utility effect related to its element, at the GM’s discretion.   When you use this power, or as a  power afterwards, you can attach the engine to a weapon you touch. Strikes with that weapon deal an extra 1d6 damage of the chosen trait. A weapon can only have one engine attached to it at a time.                                           Shock Net                                   Novice                    Send Shock                                                     Electricity               All targets restrained by your Shock Net take 1d6 damage.                                 Attack              Electricity              Encounter                                Range         60 feet              Area         5-foot burst              Duration         1 minute                  Make an Intellect attack roll against your target’s Defense.      Critical Success   Your target takes 2d6 damage and is restrained   Success   Your target takes 1d6 damage and is restrained   You can use the Send Shock power.                                           Universal Gadget                                   Novice                                Concentrate              Daily              Manipulate                                Duration         1 minute                  You learn a Novice talent of your choice from any class. This talent cannot have the Daily trait.                                           Upgrade Weapon                                   Novice                                Concentrate              Manipulate                                Target         One weapon you can reach              Duration         1 hour, or until you use this power again                  Strikes with your target have a +1 bonus. When you use this power, choose one of the following effects.      Deadly Critical   Critical successes on Strikes with your target deal an extra 2d12 damage   Extended Reach   Melee Strikes with your target have an extra 5 feet of reach   Flaming Weapon   Strikes with your target deal an extra 1d6 Fire damage   Freezing Weapon   Strikes with your target deal an extra 1d6 Cold damage   Heavy Impact   Successes on Strikes with your target push creatures back 5 feet   Shocking Weapon   Strikes with your target deal an extra 1d6 Electricity damage                                           Overload                                   Veteran                                Attack              Daily              Fire                                Requirements         You must center the area of this power on a creature or object that is affected by one of your Inventor powers              Range         60 feet              Area         20-foot burst                  Dispel the chosen Inventor power. Make an Intellect attack roll against your target’s Agility DC.                            Success         Your target takes (8d6 + 2 * your Inventor level) damage                   Failure         Your target takes half damage                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Ribbons                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Mystery Potion                                   Ribbon                                Encounter               You produce a mystery potion that you brewed previously. The GM should roll on a random potion table to determine the effect, such as the table here. The potion only contains enough for 1 dose, and it becomes inert after 24 hours.                                           Robot Servant                         Ribbon                 You have constructed a robotic servant that obeys you commands. Your servant loyally follows orders you give them, even if those orders are insane or suicidal put them in extreme danger. As a robot, your servant is incapable of advanced thought or social interaction, and may interpret orders overly literally. If combat stats are necessary, your servant is a Minion commoner, except it has no Spirit score and is immune to Mental effects.                                           Tinker                                   Ribbon                                  Duration         1 hour                  You construct a small device out of spare parts. The device malfunctions and falls apart when the duration ends. Choose one of the following options.      Clockwork Toy   This toy is a clockwork animal, monster, or person that slowly clatters along the ground and makes noise that imitates the creature it represents   Fire Starter   The device produces a miniature flame, which you can use to light a small fire   Music Box   When opened, this music box plays a single song at a moderate volume",
        "url": "/inventor.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Rogue",
        "excerpt": "Rogues are sneaky fighters who prefer trickery to fighting fair. They are experts in twisting combats to their advantage, distracting and misdirecting enemies. Most rogues favor stealth and surprise attacks over direct combat. Rogues have a generally negative reputation as thieves, liars, and assassins.   Rogue talents give many ways to confuse or avoid enemies. They also include ways to exploit a distraction for all it’s worth, with powerful sneak attacks and finishing moves. Rogue talents also let them escape danger through luck or stealth. Rogue ribbons give more ways to sneak around and avoid getting caught.   Examples of rogues in fiction include Han Solo from Star Wars, Batman from DC Comics, Jack Sparrow from Pirates of the Carribean, and Corvo Attano from Dishonored.     Powers          Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Lucky                  Novice                                      You have supernaturally good luck that kicks in when it’s needed most                                               Misdirect                  Novice                                                              You confuse an enemy, causing it to hit its ally instead                                               Poison Blade                  Novice                                                              You poison your blade, making your attacks more deadly                                               Smoke Bomb                  Novice                                                              You detonate a smoke bomb and run to clear the area                                               Sneak Attack                  Novice                                                              You take advantage of your enemy to strike for extra damage                                               Death Attack                  Veteran                                      You deal massive damage against enemies you sneak attack                                               Ambush Master                  Ribbon                                      You are always ready to jump into fights and surprise enemies                                               Fast Hands                  Ribbon                                                              You can disarm traps or pickpocket others incredibly quickly                                               Unreadable                  Ribbon                                      You can lie without any way to prove you aren’t telling the truth                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          Talents                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  Lucky                         Novice                                Fortune               You have three luck points. You can spend a luck point to reroll any die roll that you make, or to reroll any attack roll against you. You regain all your luck points when you finish an 8-hour rest.                                           Misdirect                                   Novice                                Encounter                                Trigger         You are targeted by a Strike                  Make a Spirit+Perform roll. If your roll beats the attack roll of the triggering Strike, the triggering Strike targets a creature adjacent to you instead of you.                                           Poison Blade                                   Novice                                Encounter              Poison                                Target         A weapon you’re wielding that deals Piercing or Slashing damage              Duration         1 minute                  The next time you succeed on a Strike with the targeted weapon, you deal an extra 4d6 damage.                                           Smoke Bomb                                   Novice                                Encounter                                Duration         1 minute                  A cloud of smoke explodes in a 20-foot burst around you, making it impossible to see through the area. Use the Stride power.                                           Sneak Attack                                   Novice                 Make a Strike against a flat-footed creature. The weapon you Strike with must be a Finesse weapon or a ranged weapon. The base damage of the triggering Strike increases by 2d6.                                           Death Attack                         Veteran                                  Prerequisites         Sneak Attack                  The damage bonus of your Sneak Attack talent is 4d6 instead of 2d6.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Ribbons                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          Ambush Master                         Ribbon                 During the first round of combat, all creatures are flat-footed to you.                                           Fast Hands                                   Ribbon                 Use the Interact power to do some task involving an Agility+Thievery roll.                                           Unreadable                         Ribbon                 You have advantage on Spirit rolls made to lie to other people. When you’re targeted by an effect that reveals whether you’re lying, you choose the effect’s result.",
        "url": "/rogue.html"
      }
      
